      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>Malcolm Rutherford Thorpe (b. March 12,1891, d. June 24,1958). BA Yale 1913, PhD Yale 1916. Asst. in Paleo. 1919-22; Asst. Cur. Vert. Paleo. 22-27; Curator Vert. Paleo. 27-38; Acting Director PM 1927. Res. Fellow Vert. Paleo. 22-23 and Res. Assoc. Vert. Paleo. 23-38. Mack as he was known to friends was one of the most active students of fossil mammals at the YPM during the period of intensive work on the Marsh collections following WW I. It was during his curatorship that Brontosaurus was mounted in the Great Hall and the planning and supervision of its erection was largely his.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Description of the Material</head>
         <p>The archives of Malcolm Rutherford Thorpe include coresspondence and manuscript materials relating to the Yale collection.</p>  
